This paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category as it focuses on access control policies and their potential impact on security. It may also belong to the cs.DB (Databases) sub-category as it deals with mining policies from access control lists. Additionally, the use of decision trees suggests that it may belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. Finally, the potential for policy automation suggests that it may also belong to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category.
